Usage: timer_test [options]

  This program is a demonstration of R-Car Timer API that based on CMT/TMU module.

  Options:
    --module=[string]     Select cmt or tmu
    --tmode=[string]      Select test mode, there are two modes available: gettime and settime (default)
    --period_sec=[int]    Select expiration time in second unit
    --period_nsec=[int]   Select expiration time in nanosecond unit

  Note:
    1) No need to set option period_sec and period_nsec in gettime mode
    2) Default expiration time is set to 100 milliseconds

  Example:
    1) Select CMT module, test mode is settime, expiration time is 1.5 second
       # timer_test --module=cmt --period_sec=1 --period_nsec=500000000
    2) Select TMU module, test mode is settime, expiration time is 123456789 nanosecond
       # timer_test --module=tmu --period_sec=0 --period_nsec=123456789
    3) Select CMT module, test mode is gettime
       # timer_test --module=tmu --tmode=gettime
